-- OPEC agrees to raise output: Qatar
-- 
-- Tue Sep 11, 2007 12:02pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/11/us-opec-decision-idUSVAT00022720070911

 

 VIENNA  (Reuters) - OPEC has agreed to increase its oil output by 500,000 barrels per day from Nov 1, Qatari Oil Minister Abdullah al-Attiyah said on Tuesday, in a gesture to consumer nations' worried by rapidly diminishing fuel stocks and the economic impact of $77 oil. 

 (OPEC newsroom)